<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>They recently sparked speculation that they have already tied the knot in secret after announcing their engagement in July. </p>

<p>And Brooklyn Beckham and his fiancée Nicola Peltz looked more loved-up than ever as they shared a sweet selfie together on Saturday night.</p>

<p>The photographer, 21, embraced the actress, 25, and planted a kiss on her cheek as she stared at the camera.</p>

<p>Cute: Brooklyn Beckham and his fiancée Nicola Peltz looked more loved up than ever as they shared a sweet snap together on Saturday night</p>

<p>Love: The son of former footballer David Beckham showed his appreciation for his bride-to-be as he captioned the shot 'My best friend' along with a heart emoji</p>

<p>The son of former footballer David Beckham showed his appreciation for his bride-to-be as he captioned the shot 'My best friend' along with a heart emoji.</p>

<p>The snap was also shared on Nicola's Instagram account, where Brooklyn was quick to comment, saying: 'I will look after you forever'.</p>

<p>Brooklyn donned a smart white shirt in the snap while his love appeared to be wearing a beige cross over dress teamed with natural makeup. </p>

<p>Rumours: The couple recently sparked speculation that they have already tied the knot in secret after announcing their engagement in July</p>

<p>The cosy post comes after earlier this week DJ Fat Tony insisted he wants to perform at their forthcoming nuptials.</p>

<p>The musician spoke candidly about his intentions on Fubar Radio's Access All Areas show, and also gushed about his friendship with the family.</p>

<p>Chatting with Bobby Norris and Stephen Leng, Tony, 54, said of potentially hitting the decks at the wedding: 'Who knows about that. If I'm not there's going to be bloody trouble, let's just say that!' </p>

<p>Couple: Brooklyn and Nicola have kept their Instagram accounts full of sweet snaps together in recent months </p>

<p>The socialite also spoke about his close relationship with the Beckham family as he went on: 'I love Victoria and I love David and love all the kids. They get a raw deal man sometimes and all they do is good things. </p>

<p>'They are an incredible family… and those kids are the most charming kids you'll ever want to meet, so polite. </p>

<p>'And there's no like, I'm Romeo Beckham, there's none of that stuff whatsoever. It's incredible, it really is.'</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Married? Last month, Brooklyn set tongues wagging when he showed off a gold band on his wedding finger, before calling the blonde 'my wife' </p>

<p>Last month, Brooklyn set tongues wagging when he showed off a gold band on his wedding finger, fuelling speculation they've married in secret.</p>

<p>Appearing to confirm the union, the London native commented 'my wife' on a smitten snap of the pair - which Nicole had captioned 'My forever'.  </p>

<p>MailOnline contacted representatives for Brooklyn and Nicola for comment at the time. </p>

<p>'If I'm not there's going to be trouble!': Earlier this week, DJ Fat Tony, a friend of the Beckhams, insisted he wants to perform at their forthcoming nuptials (pictured in August)</p>

<p>Sweet: Brooklyn took to Instagram in July to announce his engagement to Nicola following reports he had popped the question to his 'soulmate' after just eight months of dating </p>
